CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1783720151
OL,3,CIs this the hottest Wimbledon on
OL,4,Crecord?
OL,6,FRecent climate analyses indicate that
OL,7,Faverage temperatures during Wimbledon
OL,8,Fhave increased by about 2.5C since
OL,9,F1970.
OL,11,FThe highest ever recorded temperature
OL,12,Fat the tournament was 35.7C on 1 July
OL,13,F2015. Last year, we had our hottest
OL,14,Ffirst day of Wimbledon on record.
OL,16,FTemperatures peaked at 34.5C (35C) on
OL,17,FThusday at nearby Kew Gardens.
OL,19,FThe Met Office do not have an official
OL,20,Fweather observation site at Wimbledon
OL,21,Fitself, and rely on sites nearby.
OL,26,@pD@\OX
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
