OL,3,CIs this the hottest Wimbledon on
OL,4,Crecord?
OL,6,FThe Centre Court roof provides shelter
OL,7,Ffrom rain and, for longer matches,
OL,8,Flight when it fades, but not air
OL,9,Fconditioning - something we've heard
OL,10,Fall about during the World Cup
OL,11,Ftournaments in huge US stadiums.
OL,13,FIf it's already hot and humid outside
OL,14,Fwhen the roof closes, the humidity
OL,15,Finside may initially rise due to the
OL,16,Fpeople and the enclosed air, but the
OL,17,Fventilation and dehumidification
OL,18,Fsystems are designed to counteract
OL,19,Fthis.
OL,21,FWhat does this heat mean for players?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
